WEBVTT

00:05.482 --> 00:07.194
Previously on Rectify...

00:07.236 --> 00:09.882
No one put words in your mouth.

00:09.883 --> 00:12.378
No one coerced your confession.

00:12.379 --> 00:16.332
I just said what I needed
to say to get out.

00:16.334 --> 00:18.739
I don't want you to have to
sell things to get money.

00:18.740 --> 00:20.740
I'm selling things because
I don't want them, Mom.

00:20.741 --> 00:22.741
I'm trying to simplify my life.

00:22.742 --> 00:23.920
When your mother left...

00:23.921 --> 00:26.526
I sure didn't do what I could have
to save the marriage.

00:26.527 --> 00:28.875
I just hope you do all you can
to save yours.

00:29.180 --> 00:31.031
You go off to your weekly shower,

00:31.032 --> 00:33.599
You can fight it, but you can't stop it.

00:33.600 --> 00:36.262
I guess as quickly as they appear,
they are gone.

00:36.263 --> 00:38.263
The one thing I'm sure of,

00:38.264 --> 00:42.123
is that you are dirty here someunder,
and I'm gonna find out how dirty.

00:42.574 --> 00:44.834
He almost killed you, Daniel.

00:45.215 --> 00:47.668
You can't let him get away
with what he did to you.

00:47.669 --> 00:49.919
Who says that he's getting away with it?

00:51.298 --> 00:53.400
It was lukewarm.

00:53.401 --> 00:54.533
DR. MILCH: The shower?

00:54.534 --> 00:55.796
Yes.

00:56.603 --> 01:00.636
But I would always focus
on the warm instead of the luke.

01:02.042 --> 01:03.562
It was, um...

01:04.444 --> 01:05.739
It was what?

01:06.980 --> 01:08.460
My refuge.

01:08.783 --> 01:12.185
How long has the water been on
on this day, Daniel?

01:12.186 --> 01:14.953
Oh, you only have five minutes
and then the water

01:14.954 --> 01:19.159
automatically shuts off,
so I would try not

01:19.160 --> 01:23.565
to think of the time or where I was.

01:27.635 --> 01:29.092
What's happening now?

01:29.470 --> 01:31.891
I thought it was the guards at first.

01:32.809 --> 01:35.201
But they sounded different somehow.

01:40.547 --> 01:42.986
It was like I knew before I knew.

01:44.373 --> 01:48.086
Try to stay focused
on the event, the experience,

01:48.087 --> 01:52.576
what you feel, what you see,
what you hear in the moment.

01:57.498 --> 02:01.839
Footsteps. I hear footsteps.

02:02.395 --> 02:04.837
Almost as I turn around,
somebody hits me

02:04.838 --> 02:06.287
in the back of the head.

02:06.806 --> 02:07.907
Do you see him?

02:08.609 --> 02:10.668
Now I do. I see all of them.

02:11.544 --> 02:12.745
How many?

02:12.746 --> 02:13.912
Five.

02:13.913 --> 02:15.202
Do you know them?

02:16.216 --> 02:18.508
Four of them... I knew four of them.

02:18.853 --> 02:22.256
One was executed
when I was still inside.

02:22.257 --> 02:22.990
And one was...

02:27.026 --> 02:30.574
One lived right beside me
for more than a decade.

02:31.364 --> 02:33.031
I know it's difficult,

02:33.032 --> 02:35.644
but try to stay in the present tense.

02:38.071 --> 02:42.674
I try to hit him in the face,
but I-I-I can't reach him

02:42.675 --> 02:45.970
because somebody's kicking
my legs out from under me.

02:47.014 --> 02:48.724
I'm on the ground now, and it...

02:49.390 --> 02:51.510
feels like I'm going to sleep.

02:52.441 --> 02:53.819
To sleep?

02:53.820 --> 02:58.225
Someone's cutting off
the blood supply to my brain

02:58.833 --> 03:02.689
and then... darkness.

03:05.246 --> 03:08.873
When I come to, there's, uh...
there's something in my mouth.

03:09.570 --> 03:10.837
Something?

03:10.838 --> 03:13.706
A rag... A dirty washrag.

03:13.707 --> 03:18.179
It tastes of soap
and chlorine and... and me.

03:22.949 --> 03:24.750
What are you experiencing?

03:24.751 --> 03:26.916
Pressure on my neck.

03:27.620 --> 03:34.468
Someone has their, their foot
on my neck and on my back.

03:35.963 --> 03:38.122
They're pulling my legs apart.

03:39.132 --> 03:43.957
I can't move. I can't fight.

03:45.972 --> 03:47.559
I can't scream.

03:51.278 --> 03:56.015
And now there's this weight
on top of me, crushing me.

03:56.016 --> 03:58.232
It's... It's difficult to breathe.

03:59.720 --> 04:01.047
And then...

04:03.702 --> 04:05.162
it starts.

04:07.314 --> 04:09.652
You pray that they will kill you,

04:10.631 --> 04:13.366
that there will be mercy
bestowed upon you

04:13.367 --> 04:15.168
by the merciless.

04:22.875 --> 04:26.462
The water is shut off.
My five minutes are up.

04:28.148 --> 04:31.316
Now I hear everything.

04:31.317 --> 04:33.038
What do you hear?

04:34.120 --> 04:40.993
Grunting and... and... and
laughing and, uh, encouragement.

04:40.994 --> 04:42.362
Encouragement?

04:42.363 --> 04:44.130
Someone giving another encouragement

04:44.131 --> 04:45.832
like a sports team.

04:45.833 --> 04:49.728
"Get it, boy, get it. Get some of that."

04:51.704 --> 04:54.040
Now someone is whining.

04:54.041 --> 04:55.408
"Why do I have to go last?"

04:55.409 --> 04:58.602
"Shut up, asshole, or you'll be next."

05:00.714 --> 05:02.734
Now the weight has been lifted.

05:04.184 --> 05:05.888
I can breathe again.

05:06.854 --> 05:08.191
But then, uh...

05:15.194 --> 05:18.655
someone spreads me apart again
and spits into me.

05:20.867 --> 05:23.701
And then the weight again on top of me.

05:28.208 --> 05:31.043
What is it? What's happening?

05:31.044 --> 05:32.245
(WATER DRIPPING)

05:32.246 --> 05:34.026
I hear it first.

05:34.814 --> 05:36.051
Hear what?

05:36.883 --> 05:38.902
I open my eye,

05:40.319 --> 05:42.798
the one not pressed into the floor.

05:44.391 --> 05:46.858
- What do you see?
- (DRIPPING CONTINUES)

05:46.859 --> 05:49.609
Up above, there's this... this spigot.

05:50.831 --> 05:54.132
Drops from the spigot coming down.

05:54.133 --> 05:56.843
They catch the light just... just so.

05:57.838 --> 06:01.320
They almost look like diamonds
falling from the sky.

06:03.744 --> 06:05.276
They're so close.

06:06.045 --> 06:08.536
I struggle to move my head...

06:09.215 --> 06:10.654
just an inch.

06:11.318 --> 06:13.829
With all my might, less than an inch.

06:15.956 --> 06:19.382
There. Right there.

06:21.729 --> 06:23.103
The drops.

06:24.198 --> 06:27.226
They now fall into my open eye.

06:28.234 --> 06:29.903
Blessed drops...

06:32.806 --> 06:35.141
and I wait for the next,

06:36.910 --> 06:42.380
and the next, and the next.

06:42.381 --> 06:44.575
That's all I see now,

06:45.818 --> 06:47.842
all I hear,

06:51.124 --> 06:52.716
all I feel.

06:56.496 --> 06:58.639
Nothing else is real.

